# Roadmaps

This repo runs scheduled agents that autonomously implement work
items from a structured backlog against a staging environment.

## The unified roadmap

### [`docs/roadmap/`](./roadmap/)

All roadmap-tracked work lives in a single directory with a unified
`BACKLOG.yml` (version 2 schema). The backlog contains multiple
**tracks**, each with its own meta, items, and scheduled agent.

**Where to look:**
- [`docs/roadmap/README.md`](./roadmap/README.md) -- orientation + conventions
- [`docs/roadmap/BACKLOG.yml`](./roadmap/BACKLOG.yml) -- the unified queue
- [`docs/roadmap/AGENT_PROMPT.md`](./roadmap/AGENT_PROMPT.md) -- runtime
  contract for all roadmap agents (parameterized by `TRACK`)
- [`docs/roadmap/AUTOMATION.md`](./roadmap/AUTOMATION.md) -- design,
  permissions model, recovery procedures
- [`docs/roadmap/epics/`](./roadmap/epics/) -- epic-level specs
- [`docs/roadmap/items/`](./roadmap/items/) -- per-item specs

### [`docs/roadmap-adhoc/`](./roadmap-adhoc/) -- Ad-hoc issues

**Goal:** pick up GitHub issues from collaborators that aren't
part of any roadmap. Bug reports, small feature requests,
miscellaneous fixes -- work that doesn't justify a backlog entry.

**How it picks issues:** queries GitHub for the **oldest open
issue** that lacks any roadmap or ad-hoc label. The issue body
itself is the spec -- the agent analyzes it for coherence,
solvability, and clarity before implementing.

**Where to look:**
- [`docs/roadmap-adhoc/README.md`](./roadmap-adhoc/README.md) -- full description + state machine
- [`docs/roadmap-adhoc/STATE.yml`](./roadmap-adhoc/STATE.yml) -- in-flight items only
- [`docs/roadmap-adhoc/AGENT_PROMPT.md`](./roadmap-adhoc/AGENT_PROMPT.md) -- runtime contract

## How agents coexist

Same code base, same staging env, separate everything else:

- Each track agent operates on its own section of `BACKLOG.yml`
- The ad-hoc agent operates on GitHub issues + `STATE.yml`
- One in-progress item per agent at any time
- All agents share CI workflows and staging deploy infrastructure
- No cross-track item dependencies

## Kill switches

To pause agent work without touching schedules:

- Pause a roadmap track: set `tracks.<name>.meta.locked: true` in
  `docs/roadmap/BACKLOG.yml`, commit + push to `${__PROD_BRANCH}`.
- Pause the ad-hoc agent: set `meta.locked: true` in
  `docs/roadmap-adhoc/STATE.yml`.

Each agent reads its kill switch first thing on every tick and exits
cleanly if true.

## Adding a new track

1. Add a key under `tracks:` in `docs/roadmap/BACKLOG.yml` with
   its own `meta:` and `items:` sections.
2. Pick a unique ID prefix, branch prefix, and issue label.
3. Create the issue label in GitHub.
4. Schedule an agent with `TRACK` set to the new key.
5. Update this file with the new track's entry.
